{"title_page": "Karamdaata (1986 film)", "text_new": "{{Notability|Films|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Karamdaata (1986)\n| image          = Karamdaata 1986 film.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Shashilal K. Nair]]\n| producer       = \n| story          = \n| screenplay     = [[Sardar Talukdar]]\n| writer         = ''Sardar Talukdar''\n<br/>\n| starring       = [[Shammi Kapoor]]<br/>\n[[Shakti Kapoor]]<br/>\n[[Mithun Chakraborty]]<br/>\n[[Amrita Singh]]<br/>\n[[Dinesh Hingoo]]<br/>\n[[Raj Kishore]]<br/>\n[[Kiran Kumar]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/aditya-raj-kapoor-ages-from-30-to-65-years-in-his-next/1110638/ |title=Aditya Raj Kapoor ages from 30 to 65 years in his next|newspaper=The Indian Express|date=3 May 2013|first=Krutika|last=Behrawala|accessdate=14 February 2020}}</ref>\n| music          = [[Anu Malik]]\n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| studio         = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = 1986\n| runtime        = \n| country        = India\n| language       = [[Hindi language|Hindi]]\n| budget         = \n| gross          =\n}}\n'''''Karamdaata''''' (Hindi: \u0915\u0930\u094d\u092e\u0926\u093e\u0924\u093e) is a 1986 Indian [[Hindi language|Hindi-language]] [[Drama (film and television)|drama film]] directed by [[Shashilal K. Nair]], screenplayed and written by [[Sardar Talukdar]]. Starring [[Shammi Kapoor]], [[Shakti Kapoor]], [[Mithun Chakraborty]], [[Amrita Singh]], [[Dinesh Hingoo]] and other characters, [[Raj Kishore]] and [[Kiran Kumar]] also play lead roles in the film. Its music is composed by [[Anu Malik]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/Leisure/n47yWjW7ntGx4RmNzyTMCL/Ten-actors-with-the-maximum-releases-in-a-year.html?facet=amp |title=Ten actors with the maximum releases in a year |website=livemint.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cinestaan.com/movies/karamdaata-6137/cast-crew |title=Karamdaata (1986) Cast Crew |website=cinestaan.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bollywoodmdb.com/movies/karamdaata/15479 |title=Karamdaata (1986) - BollywoodMDB |website=bollywoodmdb.com}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nNeeta, a daughter of Rai Bahadur, a rich industrialist, defied his wish and married a street smart Ajit. Unable to fulfill all of Ajits monetary demands, Neeta commits suicide leaving her daughter Pinky to Rai Bahadur. Due to a tiff between Rai Bahadur and Pinky, Pinky leaves her house and starts living with a taxi driver, Govinda.\n\n== Cast ==\n[[Shammi Kapoor]]<br/>\n[[Mithun Chakraborty]]<br/>\n[[Amrita Singh]]<br/>\n[[Shakti Kapoor]]<br/>\n[[Dinesh Hingoo]]<br/>\n[[Raj Kishore]]<br/>\n[[Kiran Kumar]]\n\n== Soundtrack ==\nAnnu Malik\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|id=0426059}}\u2013\n\n== References ==\n<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in India]]\n[[Category:1980s crime drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian crime drama films]]\n[[Category:1986 films]]\n[[Category:1980s Hindi-language films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Notability|Films|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Karamdaata (1986)\n| image          = Karamdaata 1986 film.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Shashilal K. Nair]]\n| producer       = \n| story          = \n| screenplay     = [[Sardar Talukdar]]\n| writer         = ''Sardar Talukdar''\n<br/>\n| starring       = [[Shammi Kapoor]]<br/>\n[[Shakti Kapoor]]<br/>\n[[Mithun Chakraborty]]<br/>\n[[Amrita Singh]]<br/>\n[[Dinesh Hingoo]]<br/>\n[[Raj Kishore]]<br/>\n[[Kiran Kumar]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/aditya-raj-kapoor-ages-from-30-to-65-years-in-his-next/1110638/ |title=Aditya Raj Kapoor ages from 30 to 65 years in his next|newspaper=The Indian Express|date=3 May 2013|first=Krutika|last=Behrawala|accessdate=14 February 2020}}</ref>\n| music          = [[Anu Malik]]\n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| studio         = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = 1986\n| runtime        = \n| country        = India\n| language       = [[Hindi language|Hindi]]\n| budget         = \n| gross          =\n}}\n'''''Karamdaata''''' (Hindi: \u0915\u0930\u094d\u092e\u0926\u093e\u0924\u093e) is a 1986 Indian [[Hindi language|Hindi-language]] [[Drama (film and television)|drama film]] directed by [[Shashilal K. Nair]], screenplayed and written by [[Sardar Talukdar]]. Starring [[Shammi Kapoor]], [[Shakti Kapoor]], [[Mithun Chakraborty]], [[Amrita Singh]], [[Dinesh Hingoo]] and other characters, [[Raj Kishore]] and [[Kiran Kumar]] also play lead role in the film. Its music is composed by [[Anu Malik]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/Leisure/n47yWjW7ntGx4RmNzyTMCL/Ten-actors-with-the-maximum-releases-in-a-year.html?facet=amp |title=Ten actors with the maximum releases in a year |website=livemint.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cinestaan.com/movies/karamdaata-6137/cast-crew |title=Karamdaata (1986) Cast Crew |website=cinestaan.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bollywoodmdb.com/movies/karamdaata/15479 |title=Karamdaata (1986) - BollywoodMDB |website=bollywoodmdb.com}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nNeeta, a daughter of Rai Bahadur, a rich industrialist, defied his wish and married a street smart Ajit. Unable to fulfill all of Ajits monetary demands, Neeta commits suicide leaving her daughter Pinky to Rai Bahadur. Due to a tiff between Rai Bahadur and Pinky, Pinky leaves her house and starts living with a taxi drive Govinda.\n\n== Cast ==\n[[Shammi Kapoor]]<br/>\n[[Mithun Chakraborty]]<br/>\n[[Amrita Singh]]<br/>\n[[Shakti Kapoor]]<br/>\n[[Dinesh Hingoo]]<br